<br>
Trader Satchels are already available, with 10 slot GIANT capacity. I have 9 in the bank along with my Deluxe sewing kit. Much nicer for bank slots than about any other 10 slot item, except for the weight of 25.<br>
<br>
The Bazaar and trader commands are already set, and if you look them over, they will make shopping in the bazaar almost like doing a search for books on Amazon.com.<br>
<br>
/bazaar welcome<br>
Tells how many traders and items for sell in the zone<br>
/bazaar search (Player name)<br>
Tells what that player has for sell, price, and description.<br>
/bazaar search (item name)<br>
tells name of all players selling that item along with prices and descriptions.<br>
/bazaar search (race)<br>
Tells all players selling items for that race along with prices and decriptions. Prices and descritions come with all searches<br>
/bazaar search (slot)<br>
Tells all players selling items for that slot.<br>
/bazaar search (class)<br>
tells all players selling items for that class<br>
/bazaar search (Stat)<br>
All players selling items with that stat<br>
/bazaar search (race) (class) (slot) (Stat)<br>
tells names of all players selling items that fit all the search criteria.<br>
/bazaar search<br>
All players and all items for sell. Can be cut short if too many people<br>
/bazaar list<br>
All players and how many items they have for sell<br>
<br>
/trader Welcome<br>
Same as bazaar welcome.How many players selling and how many items for sale<br>
/Trader new<br>
Essntially turns you into an NPC vendor. Need to set items for sell and prices AFTER using this command<br>
/trader list <br>
list all items you have for sale, prices and descriptions<br>
/trader quit<br>
turns you back into a player instead of a vendor<br>
/trader add<br>
Adds the item on your cursor to your list of items for sale<br>
/trader edit (price) (description)<br>
Allows you to set price of items on your trade list and to offer a description to the buyer.<br>
/trader delete<br>
removes the item on your cursor from your wares list<br>
<br>
So, the Bazaar will in fact make EC tunnels a barren wastleland once the commands go live. But considering how much cash and items are going to be going through here, I suspect Verant is waiting until the system is bugproof completely until they let us have it. How upset would you be if you sold your prized iksar ceremonial BP for 20pp?<br>
